# .npmrc for pnpm — AUTH AND REGISTRY ONLY
#
# ⚠️ pnpm reads only auth and registry settings from .npmrc. Putting
# `ignore-scripts=true`, `save-exact=true`, or any other behavior setting
# here is a SILENT NO-OP. Those settings live in pnpm-workspace.yaml.
# See https://pnpm.io/npmrc for the exact list of keys pnpm reads here.
#
# This file is an auth-warning template. The interpolation pattern is safe
# to commit; the literal token is not.
#
# AUDIT BEFORE COMMIT — fail-loud check that no plaintext token is present:
#   grep -E '_authToken=npm_|_auth=|_password|email=' .npmrc        (bash)
#   Select-String -Path .npmrc -Pattern '_authToken=npm_|_auth=|_password|email='  (pwsh)
#
# If a token is in git history, ROTATE THE TOKEN FIRST, then rewrite history
# (git filter-repo --replace-text) and force-push. Assume the token is
# leaked even after rewrite — anyone who cloned the repo before still has it.
#
# Rationale: ../../references/package-managers/pnpm.md

# Safe pattern — interpolation from CI env var. Commit this form, not the literal token.
//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}

# Optional: pin the registry. Useful when you operate an internal mirror.
# registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
